The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Washington, Oct. 24: President George W. Bush today nominated White House economic adviser Ben Bernanke to succeed Alan Greenspan as chairman of the Federal Reserve, a post that will give the former Fed board governor huge sway over the worlds richest economy. ?Ben Bernanke is the right man to build on the record Greenspan has established,? Bush said. Greenspan, 79, is set to step down on January 31 after more than 18 years at the helm of the Fed.

 Mumbai, Oct. 24: Reliance Industries Ltd (RIL) today claimed that 99.9 per cent of its shareholders have voted in favour of its proposed scheme to come into effect after the company?s demerger is approved by Bombay High Court.

 Mumbai, Oct. 24: Himatsingka Seide Ltd has allotted 3.82 crore bonus shares in the ratio of one bonus share for every one held, the company has informed the BSE.

 Mumbai, Oct. 24: Gujarat Ambuja Exports Ltd will split the shares of the company in the ratio of 1:5. The board has approved the splitting of shares of Rs 10 each into five shares of Rs 2 apiece, subject to requisite approval, the company has informed the BSE.

 Mumbai, Oct. 24: Lupin has entered into an agreement with GSK Philippines. Under the agreement, Lupin will manufacture and market fixed-dose combinations of tuberculosis drugs based on WHO dosing guidelines in the Philippines through GSK.




